    Method and Description
    oracle.ateam.sample.mobile.v2.persistence.service.EntityCRUDService.getHasDataSynchActions()

    oracle.ateam.sample.mobile.v2.persistence.util.EntityUtils.refreshCurrentEntity(String, List<E>, ProviderChangeSupport)
    This method can cause an endless loop in combination with getCanonicalEntityy method. Also, the iteratorRefresh method was an awkward way to do it, including the "guessing" of iterator name. Use the new refreshEntity method instead.
